posts.subject: Considering a exodus once 8ch comes back
posts.body:
There will be a brief period where the boomers, shills, and spamposters won't be on 8/pol/ shitposting it to #1/#2 board, once the site comes back up. If enough of us care to, this could be the one and only opportunity to successfully migrate /b2/ style to a board with good moderation such as /natsoc/, /pol3/, /liberty/ or so forth. 

Oftentimes people complain about the compromised or almost-nonexistent moderation of the board since Codemonkey took it from Kampfy allowing low quality to run rampant, while attempts to go to alternatives end up slow or dying due to lack of effort or interest. Ergo, wouldn't this outage be a good opportunity to do something about it?

Reminder not to click auto-distribute due to how common CP bombs are; you'll pick those up too and you'll have to sift through/delete at least 2 GB or more worth of files from ZeroHello to get rid of them.
